### Mock Response Service Test Requests

@host = http://localhost:5000

### ============================================
### ADMIN API - Mock Management
### ============================================

### 1. List all mocks
GET {{host}}/_admin/mocks

### 2. List only active mocks
GET {{host}}/_admin/mocks?isActive=true

### 3. Get a specific mock
GET {{host}}/_admin/mocks/1

### 4. Add new mock - GET request
POST {{host}}/_admin/mocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "httpMethod": "GET",
  "route": "/api/orders",
  "statusCode": 200,
  "responseBody": "{\"orders\": [{\"id\": 1, \"total\": 250.00}, {\"id\": 2, \"total\": 180.50}]}",
  "contentType": "application/json",
  "description": "Order list",
  "isActive": true
}

### 5. Add new mock - POST request
POST {{host}}/_admin/mocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "httpMethod": "POST",
  "route": "/api/orders",
  "statusCode": 201,
  "responseBody": "{\"id\": 100, \"message\": \"Order created\", \"total\": 350.00}",
  "contentType": "application/json",
  "description": "Create new order",
  "isActive": true
}

### 6. Add new mock - Parameterized route
POST {{host}}/_admin/mocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "httpMethod": "GET",
  "route": "/api/orders/{id}",
  "statusCode": 200,
  "responseBody": "{\"id\": 1, \"status\": \"completed\", \"total\": 250.00, \"items\": [{\"name\": \"Product A\", \"price\": 250.00}]}",
  "contentType": "application/json",
  "description": "Order detail",
  "isActive": true
}

### 7. Add new mock - With query string
POST {{host}}/_admin/mocks
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "httpMethod": "GET",
  "route": "/api/search",
  "queryString": "?q=laptop",
  "statusCode": 200,
  "responseBody": "{\"query\": \"laptop\", \"results\": [{\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"Gaming Laptop\", \"price\": 1500}]}",
  "contentType": "application/json",
  "description": "Search results",
  "isActive": true
}

### 8. Update mock
PUT {{host}}/_admin/mocks/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "httpMethod": "GET",
  "route": "/api/users",
  "statusCode": 200,
  "responseBody": "{\"users\": [{\"id\": 1, \"name\": \"John Updated\"}, {\"id\": 2, \"name\": \"Jane Updated\"}]}",
  "contentType": "application/json",
  "description": "Updated user list",
  "isActive": true
}

### 9. Toggle mock active/inactive
PATCH {{host}}/_admin/mocks/1/toggle

### 10. Delete mock
DELETE {{host}}/_admin/mocks/5

### 11. Clear all mocks (CAUTION!)
# DELETE {{host}}/_admin/mocks/clear

### ============================================
### MOCK RESPONSE TESTS
### ============================================

### Test 1: User list (seed data)
GET {{host}}/api/users

### Test 2: Single user (parameterized route, seed data)
GET {{host}}/api/users/123

### Test 3: User with different ID
GET {{host}}/api/users/456

### Test 4: Product list (with category, seed data)
GET {{host}}/api/products?category=electronics

### Test 5: POST - New user (seed data)
POST {{host}}/api/users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Test 6: Undefined route (should return 404)
GET {{host}}/api/undefined/route

### Test 7: PUT request
PUT {{host}}/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "email": "updated@example.com"
}

### Test 8: DELETE request
DELETE {{host}}/api/users/1

### Test 9: Order list (if created above)
GET {{host}}/api/orders

### Test 10: Order detail (if created above)
GET {{host}}/api/orders/123

### Test 11: Search (if created above)
GET {{host}}/api/search?q=laptop

### ============================================
### EDGE CASE TESTS
### ============================================

### Test: Very long route
GET {{host}}/api/very/long/route/with/many/segments/test

### Test: Route with special characters
GET {{host}}/api/users/test@email.com

### Test: Combination with query string
GET {{host}}/api/products?category=electronics&sort=price&order=desc
